# üß≠ GitHub Training & Accreditation Roadmap

This roadmap outlines a modular path to mastering GitHub‚Äîfrom foundational skills to advanced security, automation, and governance‚Äîculminating in formal certifications.

---

## üîπ Phase 1: Foundations & Core Skills

**Goal:** Build fluency in GitHub fundamentals, collaboration, and secure workflows.

| Module / Certification     | Focus                                 | Source         | Link                                                                 |
|----------------------------|----------------------------------------|----------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| GitHub Foundations         | Core GitHub concepts, repo management | GitHub Learn   | https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/github/github-foundations/ |
| GitHub Overview            | Platform capabilities, repo lifecycle | Microsoft Learn| https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/github/                   |
| GitHub Learning Pathways   | Curated tutorials from GitHub experts | GitHub Blog    | https://github.blog/developer-skills/github/github-learning-pathways-learn-from-the-best/ |

---

## üîπ Phase 2: Automation & DevSecOps

**Goal:** Master CI/CD workflows and secure development practices.

| Module / Certification     | Focus                                 | Source         | Link                                                                 |
|----------------------------|----------------------------------------|----------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| GitHub Actions             | Workflow automation, CI/CD pipelines  | GitHub Learn   | https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/github/github-actions/   |
| GitHub Advanced Security   | Code scanning, secret detection       | GitHub Learn   | https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/github/github-advanced-security/ |
| GitHub Security Essentials | Secure DevOps practices               | GitHub Pathways| https://resources.github.com/learn/pathways/security/essentials/essentials-github-advanced-security/ |

---

## üîπ Phase 3: Administration & Governance

**Goal:** Operationalize GitHub for enterprise use, governance, and compliance.

| Module / Certification     | Focus                                 | Source         | Link                                                                 |
|----------------------------|----------------------------------------|----------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| GitHub Administration      | Enterprise repo management            | GitHub Learn   | https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/github/github-administration/ |
| GitHub Governance Pathway  | Admin & policy controls               | GitHub Pathways| https://resources.github.com/learn/pathways/administration-governance/ |

---

## üîπ Phase 4: Accreditation & Certification

**Goal:** Validate your GitHub expertise with formal credentials.

| Certification                  | Focus                          | Source       | Link                                                                 |
|--------------------------------|--------------------------------|--------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| GitHub Foundations Certification | Core GitHub skills            | GitHub Learn | https://learn.github.com/credentials#github-foundations             |
| GitHub Actions Certification     | CI/CD automation              | GitHub Learn | https://learn.github.com/credentials#github-actions                 |
| GitHub Advanced Security Certification | Secure coding practices | GitHub Learn | https://learn.github.com/credentials#github-advanced-security       |
| GitHub Administration Certification | Repo governance            | GitHub Learn | https://learn.github.com/credentials#github-administration          |
| GitHub Copilot Certification     | AI-assisted coding workflows | GitHub Learn | https://learn.github.com/credentials#github-copilot                 |

